sentences: Rena Kato (加藤 玲奈, Katō Rena, born July 10, 1997) is a Japanese idol, singer, model, and actress.
Formed in 2012, the trio released their first and only single "Ikujinashi Masquerade" with Rino Sashihara from HKT48, charting at number one in Japan.
Kato was born on July 10, 1997, in Chiba, Chiba, Japan.
Kato participated in the 10th-generation auditions held by AKB48, and joined as a kenkyuusei trainee in March 2010.
On December 17, 2011, Rena Katō, together with two other members of AKB48, Ami Maeda and Anna Iriyama, held a large autograph-signing event in Hong Kong.
It was the last issue of 2011.
In 2012, she participated in the AKB48 drama Majisuka Gakuen 3, which was a sequel to the series, but with a different storyline completely unrelated to the previous adaptations.
She was also promoted to Team 4 on March 23, 2012.
Soon after the TV series Shiritsu Bakaleya Kōkō ended on June 30, 2012, it was announced that Rena Katō would participate in its film adaptation.
She was transferred to Team B after the AKB48 Tokyo Dome Shuffle on August 24, 2012, where her then-team, the first version of Team 4, was disbanded.
In 2013, she participated on her second A-side in AKB48 on the summer single "Sayonara Crawl", which included 38 members.

On 2014, she got a knee injury and had to temporarily postpone her AKB48 activities, as a result, she was not able to participate in the Unit Matsuri 2014, as well as the AKB48 Request Hour Set List Best 200, except on the final day.
She resumed her activities on February 16, 2014.
She joined the Senbatsu for the third time in the 37th single's A-side, titled "Labrador Retriever", released on May 21, 2014.
On March 26, 2015, she was transferred to team B in AKB48 Spring Shuffle 2015 event.
On March 26, 2015, she was transferred to team B in AKB48 Spring Shuffle 2015 event.
From 2015 to 2017, Kato held annual contests called Renacchi Sōsenkyo (れなっち総選挙, "Renacchi Elections"), inspired by the AKB48 Group's Senbatsu Sōsenkyo.
On December 16, 2021, during a YouTube livestream, Kato announced her graduation from AKB48 to pursue a career as a make-up artist.
Her last theater performance was on February 14, 2022, and her final group activity will be on February 20.

At the end of 2011, while still an AKB48 trainee, she appeared on the cover of the Japanese magazine Weekly Playboy with seven other top members of AKB48 and SKE48.
She participated on her very first A-side in AKB48 on the summer single titled "Manatsu No Sounds Good!".
In 2013, she participated on her second A-side in AKB48 on the summer single "Sayonara Crawl", which included 38 members.

On 2014, she got a knee injury and had to temporarily postpone her AKB48 activities, as a result, she was not able to participate in the Unit Matsuri 2014, as well as the AKB48 Request Hour Set List Best 200, except on the final day.
On March 26, 2015, she was transferred to team B in AKB48 Spring Shuffle 2015 event.
Every year, AKB48 Group members can apply for the opportunity to take part in singles, photoshoots, and theatrical productions organized by her.
Her last theater performance was on February 14, 2022, and her final group activity will be on February 20.
